## Default Definition of Ready (DoR) for User Stories

A user story is **ready** for sprint planning when it meets these criteria:

### Essential Criteria

- [ ] **Clear user story format** - Written as: "As a [user], I want [goal], so that [benefit]"
- [ ] **Acceptance criteria defined** - Specific, testable conditions for completion
- [ ] **Estimated** - Team has sized the story (story points/t-shirt size)
- [ ] **Small enough** - Can be completed within one sprint
- [ ] **Independent** - Minimal dependencies on other stories (or dependencies identified)

### Understanding & Clarity

- [ ] **Understood by the team** - Developers can explain what needs to be built
- [ ] **Questions resolved** - No open blockers or unknowns
- [ ] **Stakeholder approved** - Product Owner has validated the requirements

### Technical Readiness

- [ ] **Technically feasible** - Team knows *how* to implement it
- [ ] **Design/UX available** (if applicable) - Mockups or wireframes ready
- [ ] **API contracts defined** (if applicable)
